On the State Program of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan "On the implementation of the Action Strategy for the five priority areas of development of the Republic of Uzbekistan in 2017-2021 in the" Year of Science, Enlightenment and Digital Economy "2020 In accordance with the Decree No. PF-5953 of March 2, 2006, further development of the e-government system through the maintenance of a single register of e-government information systems and resources, the formation of lists of single identifiers, directories and classifiers, the introduction of data management information systems, In order to introduce the procedure for electronic reporting of public authorities and organizations on their activities to the public, the Cabinet of Ministers decides: 
 1. On the State Program of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan on the implementation of the Action Strategy for the five priority areas of development of the Republic of Uzbekistan in 2017-2021 in the "Year of Science, Enlightenment and Digital Economy" »In accordance with the Decree No. PF-5953 of March 2, 2020: 
 Unified register of e-government information systems and resources (hereinafter - the single register) information system; 
 modernization of the information system of e-government identifiers, directories and lists of classifiers, which must be used in the information systems and resources of government agencies and organizations; 
 For information, measures are being taken to introduce an information system "Data Management", which will allow to analyze the socio-economic development of the country through the integration of information systems and databases of government agencies and organizations. 
 2. Note: 
 Ministries, state committees, committees, agencies, departments, local state authorities and business associations (hereinafter - state bodies and organizations) with a state share of 50% or more in the charter capital are included in the single register information systems and information resources (hereinafter - information systems); 
 government agencies and organizations are prohibited from developing and using information systems that duplicate the functional functions of information systems included in the single register. In this case, the development and use of other information systems that allow fast, convenient, efficient, cost-effective and safe use of the information system included in the single register may be allowed, as an exception, only in accordance with the conclusion of the digital economy and e-government; 
 government agencies and organizations are obliged to use e-government directories, classifiers and unique identifiers in interagency electronic cooperation. 
 3. Следующее: 
 Regulations on the procedure for formation and maintenance of the Single register of information systems and resources of the electronic government in appendix 1; 
 Regulations on the procedure for forming and maintaining the register of e-government directories and classifiers, as well as the use of single identifiers in Annex 2; 
 Annex 3 to the Regulation on the Procedure for Collection, Processing and Analysis of Data by Government Agencies and Organizations through the Information Management Information System; 
 Approve the Roadmap for the Development and Implementation of e-Government Interagency Information Systems in accordance with Annex 4. 
 4. Примечание: 
  From September 1, 2020, the procedure for electronic reporting to the public by public administration bodies, their territorial divisions, as well as the Council of Ministers of the Republic of Karakalpakstan, regional and Tashkent city khokimiyats, district (city) khokimiyats is given; 
 this procedure is of a recommendatory nature for state bodies and organizations not provided for in the second paragraph of this paragraph. 
 To approve Regulations on the procedure for the electronic reporting of the state bodies and the organizations to the public according to appendix 5. 
 5. The Ministry of Information Technologies and Communications of the Republic of Uzbekistan in conjunction with the State Inspectorate for Informatization and Telecommunications Control and the State Unitary Enterprise "Cyber Security Center": 
 to create a single register by October 1, 2020 and Development and approval of technical documentation for the modernization of the information system "Register of classifiers"; 
 Ensure the implementation of a single register and the information system "Register of e-government directories and classifiers" by January 1, 2021. 
 6. Note that: 
 The Ministry of Information Technologies and Communications of the Republic of Uzbekistan is the owner of the single register and information systems "Register of e-government directories and classifiers" and ensures its maintenance; 
 Costs associated with the creation of a single register, modernization of the information system "Register of e-government directories and classifiers" and subsequent technical support to finance interdepartmental projects of e-government and digital economy is carried out at the expense of the special account; 
 The Ministry of Economic Development and Poverty Reduction of the Republic of Uzbekistan is the customer for the development and implementation of the Information Management Information System; 
 Expenditures related to the development and implementation of the information management information system will be provided by the Reserve Fund of the Cabinet of Ministers, grants from the International Monetary Fund and international financial institutions, and support and improvement of the information system - O ' financed from the State Budget of the Republic of Uzbekistan. 
 7. To state bodies and the organizations: 
 a) till August 1, 2020 in the single register to appoint the person responsible for registration of information systems and data entry, and on the responsible person to submit information to the Ministry of Information Technologies and Communications Development of the Republic of Uzbekistan; 
 b) by August 15, 2020 in coordination with the Ministry of Information Technologies and Communications Development of the Republic of Uzbekistan, the State Inspectorate for Information and Telecommunications Control and the State Unitary Enterprise "Cyber ​​Security Center" develop and approve: 
 Take organizational and technical measures to improve their information systems, taking into account the integration with the information system "Register of e-government directories and classifiers"; 
 Registration of existing information systems and their inclusion in the single register, taking into account the fact that information on them is constantly updated; 
 Ensuring constant updating of information and data in the framework of the formation of the information system "Register of e-government directories and classifiers". 
 8. To the state inspectorate for control in the field of informatization and telecommunications of the Republic of Uzbekistan to provide regular monitoring of inclusion of all information systems of state bodies and the organizations in the single register. 
 9. The State Unitary Enterprise "Cyber Security Center" should ensure the examination of information systems of government agencies and organizations for compliance with information security requirements. 
 10. Control of execution of this resolution to assign to the adviser to the Prime Minister of the Republic of Uzbekistan - the head of Department of development of IT-technologies, telecommunications and innovative activity of the Cabinet of Ministers O.M. Umarov and Minister of Information Technologies and Communications of the Republic of Uzbekistan Sh.M. Let Sadikov be in charge.

